				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote25-10705_000_016">25.</a></span>
					<p>John Greenleaf Whittier put it simply: &ldquo;Heed how thou livest. Do not act by day which from the night shall drive thy peace away&rdquo; (&ldquo;Conduct [From the Mahabharata],&rdquo; in <span class="emphasis">The Complete Poetical Works of John Greenleaf Whittier</span> [1802], 484).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote26-10705_000_016">26.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/4.3?lang=eng#2" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 4:3</a>; emphasis added; see also Marion&nbsp;G. Romney, in Conference Report, Apr. 1967, 79&ndash;82.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote27-10705_000_016">27.</a></span>
					<p>Conscience is a moral compass pointing us toward peace. It is activated by at least two sources: the Light of Christ, a glorious birthright from our Heavenly Father (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.6-13?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 88:6&ndash;13</a>; <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">93:2</a>), and the gift of the Holy Ghost (see <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/39.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Doctrine and Covenants 39:6</a>).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote28-10705_000_016">28.</a></span>
					<p>&ldquo;Two sets of forgiveness are required to bring peace to the transgressor&mdash;one from the proper authorities of the Lord&rsquo;s Church, and one from the Lord himself. [See <a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/26.29?lang=eng#28" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 26:29</a>.]&rdquo; (<span class="emphasis">Teachings of Presidents of the Church: Spencer&nbsp;W. Kimball</span> [2006], 41).</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote29-10705_000_016">29.</a></span>
					<p>&ldquo;How Gentle God&rsquo;s Commands,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Hymns,</span> no. 125.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote30-10705_000_016">30.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/14.26-27?lang=eng#25" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">John 14:26&ndash;27</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote31-10705_000_016">31.</a></span>
					<p><a href="http://www.lds.org/scriptures/nt/john/16.33?lang=eng#32" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">John 16:33</a>.</p>
				</li>
				<li class="footnote " id="-10705_000_016"><a name="-10705_000_016">&nbsp;</a>
					<span class="label"><a name="footnote32-10705_000_016">32.</a></span>
					<p>&ldquo;Though Deepening Trials,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Hymns,</span> no. 122.</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
                                        
